      "message": "[Critical] Line 249: 🔴 Critical Issues - `start()` can still drop the early auth callback on any retry/restart because `tempAccount` is not reset before creating the new temporary account. With `authObserverInstalled` preventing a fresh subscription, callbacks emitted during the second `createTemporaryAccount()` will be compared against the previous account id and discarded instead of buffered. Reset the temporary account and pending buffer before starting creation so pre-assignment events are buffered for the new account.\n\n```suggestion\n    func start() {\n        uiState \u003d .initial\n        tempAccount \u003d nil\n        pendingAuthResults.removeAll()\n        // Install observer first so it captures events during account creation.\n        setupDeviceAuthObserver()\n        Task { @MainActor in\n```\n",
